5 sixty-five (165) days of instruction each school year, if a district
6 board of education adopts a school-hours policy and notifies the
7 State Board of Education prior to October 15 of the applicable
8 school year; or
9 4. Beginning with the 2021-2022 school year, for not less than
10 one thousand eighty (1,080) hours each school year, if a district
11 board of education adopts a school-hours policy, notifies the State
12 Board of Education prior to October 15 of the applicable school
13 year, and meets the requirements established by the State Board of
14 Education pursuant to subsection H of this section.
15 B. A school district may not count more than thirty (30) hours
16 each school year that are used for attendance of professional
17 meetings toward the one hundred eighty (180) days or one thousand
18 eighty (1,080) hours of classroom instruction time required in
19 subsection A of this section.
20 C. Teachers off contract with an employing district shall not
21 be required by the employing school district to attend professional
22 meetings unless the teacher is paid additional compensation for the
23 additional time. Teachers may be paid additional compensation for
24 attending professional meetings in excess of their contract term.
